            <p class="note-img">Changgyeonggung Palace, Seoul</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Attractions in Busan</b>: Haeundae & Gwangalli Beach; Sea Life Aquarium; BAY building - the most beautiful view of the coastal city at night; Suyeongman Cruise Center; Shinsegae Centum City - Guinness Book of Records recognized this shopping complex as "the world's largest shopping center" in 2009; Joseon Tongsinsa History Museum; Hwangnyeongsan Observatory; Busan Tower...</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Attractions in Gwangwon</b>: Nami Island; Dakgalbi Chuncheon Myeongdong Street; Chuncheon Joongang traditional market; Ocean World water park...</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Attractions in Jeju</b>: Udo Island; Aqua Planet - the country's largest aquarium; Seopjikoji - where a sea of ​​yellow mustard flowers bloom in March-April; Rimg Bijarim forest; Mazeland maze park...</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Walking tours to explore Korea: Ansan Jarakgil trail in Seoul, Jeju Olle trail, Hanyangdoseong trail...</p>
            <img src="~/Content/Images/Home/Handbook/Korea/korea-5.jpg" width="100%" />
